Gaelron,<br>
<br>
A reservation system can never work in the long-term run by players.  Players disagree, and have no real powers of enforcement.<br>
<br>
Right now there is an admirable attempt on one with Rage, but it's already showing strains.. looking at the list there are 2 to 5 new signups on each single Rage cycle.. meaning in a few months you can see a 50 person list there.  Now it's up in the air about making a cleric have to qualify for a spot on the list.... which if it hapens means, any way you cut it, it's a power play to control a spawn... but if it doesn't happen, a six month waiting list is gonna be a reality soon.<br>
<br>
The only other near-reservation is the ntov rotation, but that is a rotation between the guilds capable of farming there pretty much... so far every time someone capable has come along to break in they have.. and it exists simply because the guilds there don't want to fight over it, and all realize they cannot shut people out even if they wanted to.  Everybody on that rotation got in by breaking in, and Eternal Holiday has killed some odd dragons outside the rotation also...  <br>
<br>
The 2 central problems with this game in the raiding level is limited supply, and people blowing things out of proportion.<br>
I don't know any guild that kills mobs to screw other people over.  I rarely even see it on an individual level.  People play this game to advance, raiders kill mobs for their own benefit, for their team benefit, and for the challenge.  <br>
<br>
When someone questions a 22 person and growing list, and gets flamed and insulted and his points ignored, who is being the assholes?   I should note it's not the majority flaming, many folks in the ragefire camp admit what they are doing is flawed and most likely a temporary band aid.... and make an attempt to adress the issues.  <br>
<br>
But sqeaky wheels get all the attention.  People trying to make the system workable, and the fact that Wraith is using the system is overshadowed by folks like Laur who just like to whine whenever anyone does anything they can't do, or has something they like... because gosh darn they must be horrible people to have something or do something Laur wants!<br>
<br>
The attidude that anybody else doing something is doing it TO GET YOU is the biggest problem to overcome.   People that believe they deserve whatever toy is the flavor of the week more than you do, so you better go away and not get that toy cuz you'll be screwing them over if you do!<br>
<br>
That is the attitude that killed QQ, when many guilds expected and demanded the system work for them at the expense of being fair to others.   When Vis and LC  decided they wanted more than the system could give them if they were treated like other guilds.  <br>
When the system forgot it was just a guideline and would not compromise with those that didn't need it.<br>
<br>
bah.. the joys of insomnia...  <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
